a and cheddar cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place sausage into mixing bowl and cook <b>4 min\/250°F\/\/speed 0.5<b>. Mix well with spatula and cook a further <b>4 min\/250°F\/\/speed 1<b>. Line a bowl with paper towels. Transfer cooked sausage into bowl and let drain. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Dough"},{"content":"Place flour, water, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>, then knead <b>2 min\/<b>."},{"content":"Transfer dough to a lightly floured surface. Cut dough into six equal pieces and shape each piece into a ball. Cover with a damp paper towel and let rest 10 minutes. Meanwhile preheat oven to 425°F and line two baking sheets with parchment."},{"content":"Roll out each piece of dough into a circle (approx. 6 in.). Transfer dough circles onto prepared baking sheets and brush with oil. Prebake pizza dough for 5 minutes (425°F) before adding toppings."},{"content":"Evenly divide and spread reserved sauce over each pizza dough, leaving a ½ inch border. Top with onions, reserved cheese and reserved sausage. Crack one egg directly onto each pizza, nestled into toppings. Bake for 5-7 minutes (425°F) until eggs are set to taste and pizza edges are puffed and lightly golden. Let rest 3-5 minutes before slicing. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve hot."}],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}